---
/**
 * transactions-isolation-fundamentals · Figure 4 — Level 4, snapshot SCOPE:
 * Read Committed (per-statement) vs Snapshot Isolation (per-transaction).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/transactions-isolation/transactions-isolation-fundamentals.html (figure +
 * svg + figcaption). Lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the MDX,
 * because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attrs. No arrowhead markers are referenced here.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 150"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Read Committed takes a fresh snapshot per statement; Snapshot Isolation takes one per transaction"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="150"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">READ COMMITTED — snapshot per STATEMENT</text
            >
            <line x1="40" y1="40" x2="40" y2="120" stroke="#6b675f"></line>
            <g fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"
                ><rect x="60" y="40" width="74" height="22" rx="5"></rect><rect
                    x="60"
                    y="74"
                    width="74"
                    height="22"
                    rx="5"></rect></g
            >
            <text x="97" y="55" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9">SELECT → A</text>
            <text x="97" y="89" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9">SELECT → B≠A</text>
            <text x="150" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#9a2417"
                >non-repeatable read leaks</text
            >
            <line x1="300" y1="8" x2="300" y2="140" stroke="#d8d4c8" stroke-dasharray="4 4"></line>
            <text
                x="450"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">SNAPSHOT ISO — snapshot per TRANSACTION</text
            >
            <line x1="340" y1="40" x2="340" y2="120" stroke="#6b675f"></line>
            <g fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12"
                ><rect x="360" y="40" width="74" height="22" rx="5"></rect><rect
                    x="360"
                    y="74"
                    width="74"
                    height="22"
                    rx="5"></rect></g
            >
            <text x="397" y="55" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9">SELECT → A</text>
            <text x="397" y="89" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9">SELECT → A</text>
            <text x="450" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >frozen view; reads always agree ✓</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The single mechanical difference: snapshot <em>scope</em>. Per-statement (RC) lets the view
        move under you; per-transaction (SI) freezes it.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
